        <div class="step" id="step-3">
            <h1>✨ Chapter 3: Spirit (Contentment)</h1>
            <div class="quote">"Our greatest fear should not be of failure, but of succeeding at things in life that don’t really matter."<br /> — Francis Chan</div>
            <p>The "Inner Compass": Purpose, relationships, and faith.
                <br />“Gratitude turns what we have into enough.” - Aesop
                <br />“Contentment is the only real wealth.” - Alfred Nobel
                <br />“But godliness with contentment is great gain.”  1 Timothy 6:6
            </p>

            <div><br />📖 <B>Overview: The Inner Compass</B><br /><br />
            The Spirit dimension is about your "Why." It encompasses your faith, your sense of purpose, and the quality of your relationships. While the Body is your vessel and the Mind is your toolbox, the Spirit is the driver. When you are spiritually aligned, you experience a sense of peace and contentment that is not dependent on external circumstances.
            <br /><br />This section explores your spiritual history, your current support systems (fellowship), and your vision for the future. We will look at how you serve others and how you manage your emotional health.        
           </div>
           <br />
            
